{
  "texts": [
    "The resulting HiFi assembly mixture was transduced into Endura Electrocompetent Cells using a Gene Pulser Xcell electroporator in 1 mm cuvette with 1800 V, 10 µF, 600 Ohm program.",
    "Six electroporation reactions were performed to ensure high coverage of the entire library.",
    "After a 1 h incubation at 37 °C, transformed bacteria were plated on twelve 15 cm LB ampicillin plates and incubated overnight at 37 °C.",
    "Next, 10 mL of LB was added to each plate and the transformed bacterial colonies were recovered using sterile scrapers.",
    "Pooled bacterial colonies from three plates were transferred to 500 mL LB and grown with shaking at 37 °C for 3 h. The resulting bacterial cultures were collected and DDR-CRISPR library plasmid DNA was purified using a Qiagen plasmid DNA maxiprep kit."
  ]
}